    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Literacy indicates the overall human development index beyond just the skill to read and write. In the sub-metropolis, out of the total population of 150,450 aged 5 years and above, 114,709 or 76.24% are literate. The population that can only read is 763 or 0.51%, while the population that cannot read or write (illiterate) is 34,866 or 23.17%. The ward-wise detailed description is mentioned in the table."
    },
