    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "B) Literacy Status Based on Formal Education"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "UNESCO defined a literate person in 1956 as someone who can read and write with understanding and do basic daily calculations. Nepal also operates its literacy campaign based on this definition. In this sub-metropolis, out of the total population aged 5 to 25 years, 35,267 or 61.10% are currently attending schools or colleges, 12,799 or 22.18% previously attended schools or colleges, and 9,550 or 16.55% have never achieved formal education. Detailed descriptions are presented in the following tables."
    },
